Given the joint probability density function of random variables $X$ and $Y$:
\[
f(x,y)=\begin{cases}
24xy, & 0<x<1, 0<y<1, x+y<1 \\
0, & \text{elsewhere}
\end{cases}
\]
Calculate the probability $P(X+Y<\frac{1}{2})$. Determine the appropriate limits for the double integral to find this probability.

