Suppose \(X\) is a discrete random variable with the following probability distribution function (p.d.f):
\[
\begin{array}{c|cccc}
X & 0 & 1 & 2 & 3 \\
\hline
p(x) & \frac{2\theta}{2} & \frac{\theta}{3} & \frac{2(1-\theta)}{3} & \frac{1-\theta}{3}
\end{array}
\]
where \(0 \leq \theta \leq 1\). Given the sample \((3,0,2,1,3,2,1,0,2,1)\), find the maximum likelihood estimate (MLE) of \(\theta\).

